t* have to spawn Simon Aldicott, he is (almost) always up.<br><br>I have spent a *lot* of time wandering to and from Kith, and he has always been up when I've passed by the lake.<br><br>I got my coffin from Ping a week before I did the Reverant part, and Simon was up and ready when I finally got a crew together 7 days later and headed over that way.  So don't worry about it.<br><br>However, what's funny is that just as my crew was finally buffed and ready, *moments* before I handed Simon the coffin (I even had it on my mouse cursor already), Simon DESPAWNED!  LOL!<br><br>At the time I was horrified, I was afraid everyone was going to give up and go away and I'd have to gather another crew some other day, but just as we were sitting around debating what to do about the missing Simon, he respawned again.<br><br>I checked the EQ time when he despawned, it was 8PM, exactly &quot;dusk&quot; (coincidentally also the time that the Kith undead start spawning), so he probably just has a &quot;reset&quot; at nightfall.<br><br>The total time he was gone wasn't more than 5 minutes, tops, but it sure *felt* a lot longer...<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showPrevMessage?topicID=3146.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showNextMessage?topicID=3146.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3146.topic&index=8><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.emailToFriend?topicID=3146.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif bor